                            <comment id="17583854" author="cmccabe" created="Tue, 23 Aug 2022 21:25:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it seems like in general, deferred events should not contribute to this metric. NoOpEvent is one of them but there are some others.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17619146" author="jsancio" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2022 23:26:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;They should contribute to the metrics. The controller needs to make sure to subtract the deferred time from the computed delay.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can imagine a large number of delay events that couldn&apos;t be process for a while after they triggered.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
